### Fox — XP Bonus (Special Mechanic)

Because there is no vanilla potion effect for XP gain, the Fox passive is implemented as a custom event hook rather than a status effect. It is the only companion that works this way.

**Implementation approach (as built):**
- A single mixin on `ServerPlayer#giveExperiencePoints(int)` — every server-side XP award funnels through
  it (mob kills, mining, smelting, breeding, ...), so one `@ModifyVariable` covers all sources cleanly,
  with no per-drop event plumbing.
- It doubles the amount only when `CompanionBehavior.hasActiveCompanion(player, EntityType.FOX)` is true —
  i.e. a following (non-sitting) tamed fox owned by the player is within the 24-block follow range.
- `FoxCompanion.passiveEffect()` returns `null`, so the per-tick status-effect path does nothing for the
  fox; the bonus is entirely event-driven via the mixin. This is the only companion that works this way.

