## Mixin Strategy

Wildbound uses the **minimum possible mixins**. Taming itself needs **none** — Fabric `UseEntityCallback` detects the right-click for every animal at once. A mixin is only needed where a vanilla mob doesn't drive its movement through the goal system and we must intercept its custom AI step.

| Mixin Target | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Bat#customServerAiStep` | Hand a tamed bat to the companion framework (follow/sit + effect) and cancel vanilla wandering. Required because `Bat` ignores the goal system |
| *(ground animals)* | *(expected: none — add `FollowOwnerGoal`/`SitWhenOrderedToGoal` from `serverTickBehavior`, or a small goal-injecting mixin if a mob doesn't expose its goal selector)* |

No interaction or entity-conversion mixins are required.

