## Advancements

Per-animal advancements use a single shared trigger `wildbound:companion_tamed` that fires with the animal type as a parameter. The tree reveals **progressively**, so it can hint at itself before a player has tamed anything:

- *"Wildbound"* (the root) fires from vanilla `minecraft:inventory_changed` the moment the player first picks up **any** taming item (a flower, apple, spider eye, …). It lands early and its description teaches the mechanic — an onboarding nudge, not a reward for taming.
- *"A Growing Menagerie"* fires on the **first successful tame** and is the parent of every per-animal advancement *and* the capstone, so the capstone reads as the visible culmination of that animal cluster (MC advancements are single-parent, so the animals can't each draw a line into it — this is the closest legible layout).
- *"The Wild Knows Your Name"* (capstone) requires one tame of **every** companion type.
- Two teaching advancements hang directly off the root: *"Home on the Range"* (first wander) and *"Peace and Quiet"* (first milk-quiet).

