## First Implementation Target — Bat

### Summary
The Bat companion is the first to be implemented. All shared framework code should be written with the Bat as the proof-of-concept, then verified to be fully extensible before moving to the next animal.

### Bat-Specific Values

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Taming item | Spider Eye |
| Passive effect | Night Vision I |
| Follow | Velocity steering toward a point just above the owner's head; teleports if left >20 blocks behind |
| Sit | Prefers a sturdy ceiling within 5 blocks (hangs, reusing vanilla `setResting(true)`); else perches on the ground within 8 blocks below; hovers in place only if neither is in reach |

### Why the Bat can't use goals

Vanilla `Bat` extends `AmbientCreature` and registers **no movement goals** — its flight is hand-rolled in `customServerAiStep` (random `targetPosition` wandering), and resting pins its position in `tick()`. A `FollowOwnerGoal` would be ignored. So `BatCompanion.serverTickBehavior` (invoked via the `Bat#customServerAiStep` mixin) steers `deltaMovement` directly, mirroring vanilla's own movement math, and toggles the native resting flag for the ceiling-hang sit pose. There is no `BatFollowOwnerGoal` or `BatSitOnCeilingGoal` class.

### Implementation Order / Status
1. ✅ `WildboundAttachments` (OWNER, SITTING) + `CompanionType` contract
2. ✅ Shared `CompanionTaming` (UseEntityCallback) + `CompanionBehavior` tick driver
3. ✅ `BatCompanion` (the first concrete `CompanionType`)
4. ✅ `BatMixin` on `customServerAiStep` (only mixin needed)
5. ✅ Compiles; dedicated server boots and the mixin applies cleanly
6. ✅ Advancements + the `wildbound:companion_tamed` criterion trigger (root + bat + rabbit)
7. ✅ Rabbit companion added — validated the framework extends to a goal-based ground animal
8. ✅ Goal attachment moved to a `ServerEntityEvents.ENTITY_LOAD` hook — ground/flying/swimming
   companions need no per-animal mixin (just a `CompanionType` + registration)
9. ✅ Full roster: Panda, Armadillo, Frog, Bee, Axolotl, and Fox (the XP-bonus special case)
10. ✅ Per-animal sit poses (panda sit, armadillo roll-up, bee land, axolotl hold) + capstone advancement
11. ☐ Polish pass — see `docs/refinements.md` (bat follow-stacking/perch aim, axolotl water-follow, etc.)

